
WHAT YOU NEED BEFORE STARTING EACH DAY
NIFTY option chain data (minute-by-minute)
Columns needed per minute: Spot price, Strike, Call OI, Put OI, Call LTP, Put LTP
Strikes needed: ATM, ATM+1, ATM+2, ATM-1, ATM-2 (5 strikes total)
Note 09:15 spot as your Open Reference for the day
HOW TO FIND ATM STRIKE
Round spot to nearest 50.
Example: spot = 24,285 → ATM = 24,300

ATM+1 = 24,350 | ATM+2 = 24,400
ATM-1 = 24,250 | ATM-2 = 24,200
ENTRY RULES — CHECK EVERY MINUTE FROM 09:20
Step 1 — Check the time
Condition	Action
Before 09:20	Skip, too early
10:00 to 10:59	SKIP entire hour — do not enter any trade
After 15:15	Stop looking for new entries
Step 2 — Calculate ATM OI Difference
At the current ATM strike (offset 0):

ATM Call OI  =  oi_call at current ATM strike
ATM Put OI   =  oi_put  at current ATM strike
ATM Diff     =  |ATM Call OI − ATM Put OI|
Rule: ATM Diff must be ≥ 20 Lakh. If less → SKIP this minute.

Step 3 — Calculate Outer OI Difference
DO NOT include ATM in this calculation — only the surrounding strikes:

Outer Call OI  =  oi_call[ATM+1]  +  oi_call[ATM+2]
Outer Put OI   =  oi_put[ATM-1]   +  oi_put[ATM-2]
Outer Diff     =  |Outer Call OI − Outer Put OI|
Rule: Outer Diff must be ≥ 20 Lakh. If less → SKIP this minute.

Step 4 — Check Both Point Same Direction
ATM direction   =  CALL  if ATM Call OI < ATM Put OI
                   PUT   if ATM Put OI  < ATM Call OI
Outer direction =  CALL  if Outer Call OI < Outer Put OI
                   PUT   if Outer Put OI  < Outer Call OI
Rule: ATM direction must equal Outer direction. If they disagree → SKIP.

The direction is: whichever side has the LOWER OI — trade that side.

Step 5 — ATM Ratio Check
ATM Ratio  =  larger OI ÷ smaller OI   (at ATM only)
           =  max(ATM Call OI, ATM Put OI)  ÷  min(ATM Call OI, ATM Put OI)
Rule: ATM Ratio must be ≥ 1.5 (one side must have 50% more OI than other). If less → SKIP.

Step 6 — Outer/ATM Ratio Check (new in v23)
Outer/ATM Ratio  =  Outer Diff ÷ ATM Diff
Rule: Must be ≤ 5.0. If Outer Diff is more than 5× ATM Diff → signal is noise, SKIP.

Example: ATM Diff = 20L, Outer Diff = 110L → ratio = 5.5 → SKIP
Example: ATM Diff = 40L, Outer Diff = 120L → ratio = 3.0 → OK ✓

Step 7 — Check the Option Premium (new in v23)
Look up the LTP of the entry strike (ATM+2 for CALL, ATM-2 for PUT):

CALL trade → check close_call at ATM+2
PUT  trade → check close_put  at ATM-2
Rule: Premium must be ≥ ₹20 AND ≤ ₹180.

Below ₹20 = too cheap/illiquid
Above ₹180 = move already priced in, signal unreliable → SKIP
Step 8 — All Checks Passed → ENTER TRADE
Direction	Buy This Option
CALL (call OI was lower)	ATM+2 Call (CE) at current LTP
PUT (put OI was lower)	ATM-2 Put (PE) at current LTP
Record: Entry time, Entry premium (LTP), Entry ATM strike

WHILE IN TRADE — CHECK EVERY MINUTE
Exit A — SL Hit (check first, any time)
If current LTP  ≤  Entry Premium × 0.80
→ EXIT immediately. Loss = 20% of entry premium × 75 lots

Exit B — Target Hit (check any time)
If current LTP  ≥  Entry Premium × 2.00  (+100%)
→ EXIT immediately. Profit = entry premium × 75 lots

Exit C — Trailing Stop
Activates once: current LTP ≥ Entry Premium × 1.70 (gain of +70%)
After activation: EXIT if LTP falls back to Entry Premium × 1.20 (lock in +20%)
Exit D — OI Signal Gone (checked every minute)
Recalculate ATM Diff at current ATM strike each minute:

Current ATM Diff  =  |current ATM Call OI − current ATM Put OI|
Exit when EITHER of these persists for 2 consecutive minutes:

Condition	Name
ATM Diff drops below 20L	OI_EXIT_ATM_FELL
Both ATM Diff AND Outer Diff drop below 20L	OI_EXIT_BOTH_FELL
ATM lower side OR Outer lower side flips to opposite of trade direction	OI_EXIT_DIR_FLIP
Important rule: If only Outer Diff drops below 20L but ATM Diff is still ≥ 20L and direction still same → IGNORE, stay in trade. (Outer is noisier, ATM is the anchor.)

Exit E — Hard Exit
15:19 PM — close everything regardless of P&L.

DAILY LIMITS
Rule	Value
Maximum trades per day	3
Daily loss limit	-₹8,000 (stop entering new trades if day P&L hits this)
Cooldown after any exit	Wait 5 minutes before scanning for next entry
